<script id="friendly-deviations-template" type="text/x-jquery-tmpl">
    <h4>${Name}</h4>
    <input type="hidden" id="ChildId" value="${ChildId}" />
    <input type="hidden" id="deviationsId" value="${Id}" />
    <h5>High Income Deviation</h5>
    <p>
        Various life circumstances such as higher than average income, excess life insurance for children, sharing of tax 
        credits for the children, etc can be considered by the court in allowing or disallowing deviation. This section may be used to 
        request such deviation. You should consult the proper authority such as an attorney or tax advisor to determine eligibility.
    </p>
    <h5>Low Income Deviation</h5>
    <p>
        The Court or Jury has discretion to allow or not allow the noncustodial parent to receive a Low Income Deviation 
        that will reduce the Presumptive Amount of Child Support.  If Low Income Deviation does not apply in this case, click the “No” 
        button and proceed to the next section.
    </p>
    <div class="control-group row-fluid">
        <label class="form-question">Would the amount of Child Support payable before you apply the deviation be unjust or inappropriate?</label>
        <textarea class="input-xxlarge" cols="20" data-val="true" data-val-regex="Only alpha-numeric characters and []@@$'()!~:#&amp;_,/-?\% are allowed." data-val-regex-pattern="^(?!.*--)[A-Za-z0-9\.\?=\+\s.[\]@@$'()!~:#/&amp;_\-,\%]*$" id="Unjust" name="Unjust" placeholder="Explain" rows="2" >${Unjust}</textarea>
        <span class="field-validation-valid" data-valmsg-for="Unjust" data-valmsg-replace="true"></span>
    </div>
    <div class="control-group row-fluid">
        <label class="form-question">Would the deviation serve the best interests of the child(ren) for whom support is being determined?</label>
        <textarea class="input-xxlarge" cols="20" data-val="true" data-val-regex="Only alpha-numeric characters and []@@$'()!~:#&amp;_,/-?\% are allowed." data-val-regex-pattern="^(?!.*--)[A-Za-z0-9\.\?=\+\s.[\]@@$'()!~:#/&amp;_\-,\%]*$" id="BestInterest" name="BestInterest" placeholder="Explain" rows="2">${BestInterest}</textarea>
        <span class="field-validation-valid" data-valmsg-for="BestInterest" data-valmsg-replace="true"></span>
    </div>
    <div class="control-group row-fluid">
        <label class="form-question">
            Would the deviation seriously impair the ability of the custodial parent or non-parent custodian to 
            maintain minimally adequate housing, food and clothing for the children being supported by the order and 
            to provide other basic necessities?</label>
        <textarea class="input-xxlarge" cols="20" data-val="true" data-val-regex="Only alpha-numeric characters and []@@$'()!~:#&amp;_,/-?\% are allowed." data-val-regex-pattern="^(?!.*--)[A-Za-z0-9\.\?=\+\s.[\]@@$'()!~:#/&amp;_\-,\%]*$" id="Impair" name="Impair" placeholder="Explain" rows="2">${Impair}</textarea>
        <span class="field-validation-valid" data-valmsg-for="Impair" data-valmsg-replace="true"></span>
    </div>
    <div class="control-group row-fluid">
        <label class="form-question">
            Do you wish to apply for a Low Income or High Income Deviation?</label>
        {{if HighLow===1}}
        <label class="radio inline">High
            <input checked="checked" class="inline" data-val="true" data-val-number="The field HighLow must be a number." id="HighLow" name="HighLow" type="radio" value="1"></label>
        {{else}}
        <label class="radio inline">High
            <input class="inline" data-val="true" data-val-number="The field HighLow must be a number." id="HighLow" name="HighLow" type="radio" value="1"></label>
        {{/if}}
        {{if HighLow===2}}
        <label class="radio inline">Low
            <input checked="checked" class="inline" id="HighLow" name="HighLow" type="radio" value="2"></label>
        {{else}}
        <label class="radio inline">Low
            <input class="inline" id="HighLow" name="HighLow" type="radio" value="2"></label>
        {{/if}}
        <span class="field-validation-valid" data-valmsg-for="HighLow" data-valmsg-replace="true"></span>
    </div>
    <div class="deviation-low hide">
        <div class="control-group row-fluid">
            <label class="span4 form-question">Enter "Proposed Low Income Deviation amount" AS A POSITIVE NUMBER.</label>
            <input data-val="true" data-val-number="The field LowDeviation must be a number." data-val-regex="Amount must be a number" data-val-regex-pattern="^[0-9]*$" id="LowDeviation" name="LowDeviation" placeholder="Amount" type="text" value="${LowDeviation}">
            <span class="field-validation-valid" data-valmsg-for="LowDeviation" data-valmsg-replace="true"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="control-group row-fluid">
            <label class="span4 form-question">Explain why the noncustodial parent should be granted a Low Income Deviation.</label>
            <textarea cols="20" data-val="true" data-val-regex="Only alpha-numeric characters and []@@$'()!~:#&amp;_,/-?\% are allowed." data-val-regex-pattern="^(?!.*--)[A-Za-z0-9\.\?=\+\s.[\]@@$'()!~:#/&amp;_\-,\%]*$" id="WhyLow" name="WhyLow" placeholder="Explain" rows="2">${WhyLow}</textarea>
            <span class="field-validation-valid" data-valmsg-for="WhyLow" data-valmsg-replace="true"></span>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="deviation-high hide">
        <label class="informative">
            “Deviations are equally accepted by the court using either specific or non-specific reasons, 
            therefore you may choose to simply enter a total amount as a non-specific deviation below or click the checkbox 
            to enter one or more specific deviations</label>
        <div class="control-group row-fluid">
            <label class="span4 form-question">Non-specific Deviations</label>
            <input data-val="true" data-val-number="The field NonSpecific must be a number." data-val-regex="Amount must be a number" data-val-regex-pattern="^[0-9]*$" id="NonSpecific" name="NonSpecific" placeholder="Amount" type="text" value="${NonSpecific}">
            <span class="field-validation-valid" data-valmsg-for="NonSpecific" data-valmsg-replace="true"></span>
        </div>
        <h5>Specific Deviations</h5>
        <label class="informative">
            <p>
                Requested deviation amounts may be entered as a positive or negative number. For 
                negative numbers, add a minus sign "-" before the amount.
            </p>
            <p>
                Do not enter the TOTAL amount of monthly expenses; enter the requested amount 
                you want the court to consider as a deviation from the Presumptive Amount of Child Support.
            </p>
        </label>
        <div class="control-group row-fluid">
            <label class="span4 form-question">
                If you agree that the the Child Support Payment should be 
                modified on a monthly basis due to high income, enter the amount of increase to be applied to 
                the monthly Child Support Payment.</label>
            <input data-val="true" data-val-number="The field HighIncome must be a number." data-val-regex="Amount must be a number" data-val-regex-pattern="^[0-9]*$" id="HighIncome" name="HighIncome" placeholder="Amount" type="text" value="${HighIncome}">
            <span class="field-validation-valid" data-valmsg-for="HighIncome" data-valmsg-replace="true"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="control-group row-fluid">
            <label class="span4 form-question">Other Health Related Insurance</label>
            <input data-val="true" data-val-number="The field Health must be a number." data-val-regex="Amount must be a number" data-val-regex-pattern="^[0-9]*$" id="Health" name="Health" placeholder="Amount" type="text" value="${Health}">
            <span class="field-validation-valid" data-valmsg-for="Health" data-valmsg-replace="true"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="control-group row-fluid">
            <label class="span4 form-question">Life Insurance</label>
            <input data-val="true" data-val-number="The field Insurance must be a number." data-val-regex="Amount must be a number" data-val-regex-pattern="^[0-9]*$" id="Insurance" name="Insurance" placeholder="Amount" type="text" value="${Insurance}">
            <span class="field-validation-valid" data-valmsg-for="Insurance" data-valmsg-replace="true"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="control-group row-fluid">
            <label class="span4 form-question">Child and Dependent Care Tax Credit</label>
            <input data-val="true" data-val-number="The field TaxCredit must be a number." data-val-regex="Amount must be a number" data-val-regex-pattern="^[0-9]*$" id="TaxCredit" name="TaxCredit" placeholder="Amount" type="text" value="${TaxCredit}">
            <span class="field-validation-valid" data-valmsg-for="TaxCredit" data-valmsg-replace="true"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="control-group row-fluid">
            <label class="span4 form-question">Visitation Related Travel Expenses</label>
            <input data-val="true" data-val-number="The field Visitation must be a number." data-val-regex="Amount must be a number" data-val-regex-pattern="^[0-9]*$" id="Visitation" name="Visitation" placeholder="Amount" type="text" value="${Visitation}">
            <span class="field-validation-valid" data-valmsg-for="Visitation" data-valmsg-replace="true"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="control-group row-fluid">
            <label class="span4 form-question">Alimony PAID</label>
            <input data-val="true" data-val-number="The field Alimony must be a number." data-val-regex="Amount must be a number" data-val-regex-pattern="^[0-9]*$" id="AlimonyPaid" name="AlimonyPaid" placeholder="Amount" type="text" value="${AlimonyPaid}">
            <span class="field-validation-valid" data-valmsg-for="AlimonyPaid" data-valmsg-replace="true"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="control-group row-fluid">
            <label class="span4 form-question">Mortgage (if non-custodial parent is providing cost of home where child resides)</label>
            <input data-val="true" data-val-number="The field Mortgage must be a number." data-val-regex="Amount must be a number" data-val-regex-pattern="^[0-9]*$" id="Mortgage" name="Mortgage" placeholder="Amount" type="text" value="${Mortgage}">
            <span class="field-validation-valid" data-valmsg-for="Mortgage" data-valmsg-replace="true"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="control-group row-fluid">
            <label class="span4 form-question">Permanency Plan or Foster Care Plan</label>
            <input data-val="true" data-val-number="The field Permanency must be a number." data-val-regex="Amount must be a number" data-val-regex-pattern="^[0-9]*$" id="Permanency" name="Permanency" placeholder="Amount" type="text" value="${Permanency}">
            <span class="field-validation-valid" data-valmsg-for="Permanency" data-valmsg-replace="true"></span>
        </div>
    </div>
</script>